tory.Essays by leading historians examine the professional, social, and political functions of Italian jurists from the thirteenth to the late fifteenth centuries. The volume also examines the use of emergency powers, the critical role played by jurists in mediating the rule of law, and the adjudication of political crimes. The Politics of Law in Late Medieval and Renaissance Italy provides both an assessment of Martines' pioneering archival scholarship as well as fresh insights into the interplay of law and politics in late medieval and Renaissance Italy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aLawxPolitical aspectszItalyzFlorencexHistory. 0aLawzItalyzFlorencexHistory. 0aLawyerszItalyzFlorencexHistory. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh1 aArmstrong, Lawrin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCavallar, Osvaldo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFredona, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIsenmann, Moritz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKirshner, Julius , eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aKirshner, Julius, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKuehn, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLepsius, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartines, Lauro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartines, Lauro.1 aMenzinger, Sara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTanzini, Lorenzo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144268602140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442686021423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/